%N A398009 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} d(k^2) * log(k) / k^2, where d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%H A398009 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 377, Corollary 2.3.
%F A398009 Equals (5*Pi^2/12) * (36 * log(A) + 240*log(A_3) - log(2*Pi) - gamma), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
